    "Management": {
      "text": "Treatment is based on addressing underlying disease process\nIdiopathic edema is a diagnosis of exclusion.  Other disease process, including heart failure, cirrhosis, acute renal failure, nephrotic syndrome, chronic venous insufficiency, and medication induced edema must first be considered.\n[1]\nIdiopathic pedal edema need not to be treated with diuretics",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
    "Disposition": {
      "text": "If no respiratory symptoms, most patients may be safely discharged home\nPatients should be followed up in medical clinic for further investigation and care",
